PCRNormalizator v1.0

RDA and MB

5/11/2021

Data loading:

The input data are:

  • the matrix with Ct values for each miRNA (row) and each sample (column)
  • a sample metadata file, i.e. a tab delimited txt file with first column of sample names (matching Ct matrix’s sample names) and second column with group specifications See example files into data folder.

Step1: parsing input data for NormqPCR and load it

```r
library(reshape2)

write.table(melt(cbind(rawMirna, Detector =row.names(rawMirna)),
            id.vars       = \Detector\,
            variable.name = \Sample\,
            value.name    = \Cq\)[c(2,1,3)], 
            file = \raw.4NormqPCR.txt\,
            sep = \\t\)

```r
geNorm.NormqPCR.Res <- selectHKs(qPCR.data, method = \geNorm\,
                                   minNrHKs = 2, log =FALSE, 
# per l'opzione log, vedi https://www.researchgate.net/post/geNorm_in_NormqPCR_package_of_R
                                   Symbols = featureNames(qPCR.data),na.rm=TRUE)

### Step4: calculate cv score

<!-- rnb-text-end -->


<!-- rnb-chunk-begin -->


<!-- rnb-source-begin eyJkYXRhIjoiYGBgclxuYGBgclxuY3Yuc2FtcGxlIDwtIGFwcGx5KHJhd01pcm5hLDIsZnVuY3Rpb24oeCkgc2QoeCwgbmEucm09VFJVRSkvbWVhbih4LCBuYS5ybT1UUlVFKSlcblxuY3Yuc2NvcmUgPC0gYXBwbHkocmF3TWlybmEsMSxmdW5jdGlvbih4KSBzZCh4LCBuYS5ybT1UUlVFKS9cbiAgICAgICAgICAgICAgICAgICAgbWVhbih4LCBuYS5ybT1UUlVFKSkvXG4gICAgICAgICAgICAgICAgICAgIHN1bShjdi5zYW1wbGUpXG5gYGBcbmBgYCJ9 -->

```r
```r
cv.sample <- apply(rawMirna,2,function(x) sd(x, na.rm=TRUE)/mean(x, na.rm=TRUE))

cv.score <- apply(rawMirna,1,function(x) sd(x, na.rm=TRUE)/
                    mean(x, na.rm=TRUE))/
                    sum(cv.sample)

<!-- rnb-source-end -->

<!-- rnb-chunk-end -->

### Step5: combining all scores and calculating final Summarized Stability Score (SSS)

<!-- rnb-source-begin eyJkYXRhIjoiYGBgclxuYGBgclxuZGYucmFuayA8LSBSZWR1Y2UoZnVuY3Rpb24oZDEsIGQyKSBtZXJnZShkMSwgZDIsIGJ5ID0gXFxtaXJuYVxcLGFsbD1UUlVFKSxcbiAgICAgICBsaXN0KGRhdGEuZnJhbWUoXFxtaXJuYVxcPWdzdWIoXFxcXFxcLlxcLFxcLVxcLGdlTm9ybS5Ob3JtcVBDUi5SZXMkcmFua2luZyksXG4gICAgICAgICAgICAgICAgICAgIFxcZ2VOb3JtLm1lYW5NXFw9Yyhzb3J0KGdlTm9ybS5Ob3JtcVBDUi5SZXMkbWVhbk0pLGdlTm9ybS5Ob3JtcVBDUi5SZXMkbWVhbk1bMV0pKSwgXG4gICAgICAgICAgICBkYXRhLmZyYW1lKFxcbWlybmFcXD1nc3ViKFxcXFxcXC5cXCxcXC1cXCxuYW1lcyhyZXMubm9ybWZpbmRlciRyaG8pKSxcbiAgICAgICAgICAgICAgICAgICAgICAgXFxub3JtRmluZGVyLnJob1xcPXJlcy5ub3JtZmluZGVyJHJobyksIFxuICAgICAgICAgICAgZGF0YS5mcmFtZShcXG1pcm5hXFw9cm93Lm5hbWVzKHJhd01pcm5hKSxcbiAgICAgICAgICAgICAgICAgICAgICAgXFxjdi5zY29yZVxcPWN2LnNjb3JlKSkpICAgICAgICBcblxuICAgICAgICAgICAgXG4gICAgICAgICAgICBcbmRmLnJhbmskU1NTIDwtIHNxcnQoZGYucmFuayRnZU5vcm0ubWVhbk1eMitkZi5yYW5rJG5vcm1GaW5kZXIucmhvXjIrZGYucmFuayRjdi5zY29yZV4yKVxuZGYucmFua1stMV0gPC0gcm91bmQoZGYucmFua1stMV0sZGlnaXRzID0gNClcblxuZGYucmFuay5GIDwtIGRmLnJhbmtbb3JkZXIoZGYucmFuayRTU1MpLF1cblxuXG53cml0ZS50YWJsZShkZi5yYW5rLkYsZmlsZT1cXHN0YWJpbGl0eVNjb3JlLnR4dFxcLFxuICAgICAgICAgICAgc2VwID0gXFxcXHRcXCxxdW90ZSA9IEZBTFNFLHJvdy5uYW1lcyA9IEZBTFNFKVxuXG5cblxuZGYuRiA8LSBkZjMuU1NTW2ZpbmFscmFuayxdWzE6MTAsXVxuZGYuRiRnZU5vcm0ucmFuayA8LSBnc3ViKFxcXFxcXC5cXCxcXC1cXCxkZi5GJGdlTm9ybS5yYW5rKVxuZGYuRiRnZU5vcm0ucmFuayA8LSBmYWN0b3IoZGYuRiRnZU5vcm0ucmFuaywgbGV2ZWxzID0gZGYuRiRnZU5vcm0ucmFuaylcblxuXG5gYGBcbmBgYCJ9 -->

```r
```r
df.rank <- Reduce(function(d1, d2) merge(d1, d2, by = \mirna\,all=TRUE),
       list(data.frame(\mirna\=gsub(\\\.\,\-\,geNorm.NormqPCR.Res$ranking),
                    \geNorm.meanM\=c(sort(geNorm.NormqPCR.Res$meanM),geNorm.NormqPCR.Res$meanM[1])), 
            data.frame(\mirna\=gsub(\\\.\,\-\,names(res.normfinder$rho)),
                       \normFinder.rho\=res.normfinder$rho), 
            data.frame(\mirna\=row.names(rawMirna),
                       \cv.score\=cv.score)))        

            
            
df.rank$SSS <- sqrt(df.rank$geNorm.meanM^2+df.rank$normFinder.rho^2+df.rank$cv.score^2)
df.rank[-1] <- round(df.rank[-1],digits = 4)

df.rank.F <- df.rank[order(df.rank$SSS),]


write.table(df.rank.F,file=\stabilityScore.txt\,
            sep = \\t\,quote = FALSE,row.names = FALSE)



df.F <- df3.SSS[finalrank,][1:10,]
df.F$geNorm.rank <- gsub(\\\.\,\-\,df.F$geNorm.rank)
df.F$geNorm.rank <- factor(df.F$geNorm.rank, levels = df.F$geNorm.rank)
